description:
## Bug Report

Please answer these questions before submitting your issue. Thanks!

### 1. Minimal reproduce step (Required)
This test case may need to be executed multiple times in order to reproduce the issue. I also tested it on versions v8.5.2 and v8.5.0, and the same problem occurred.

If the SQL statement `ALTER TABLE t0 MODIFY COLUMN c1 BIGINT NOT NULL;` sometimes fails to execute, the test case will not be reproducible.

This case has been simplified by me. If it's still difficult to reproduce, I can provide a more complete test case.
```
USE test;
DROP DATABASE IF EXISTS db_1483421321;
CREATE DATABASE db_1483421321;
USE db_1483421321;
CREATE TABLE t0(c0 TINYINT);
ALTER TABLE t0 SET TIFLASH REPLICA 1;

ALTER TABLE t0 ADD COLUMN c1 DECIMAL NULL;
ALTER TABLE t0 ADD COLUMN c2 FLOAT NULL DEFAULT 0.0795439693286002;
ALTER TABLE t0 ADD COLUMN c5 DECIMAL NOT NULL;
ALTER TABLE t0 ADD COLUMN c4 DECIMAL DEFAULT 247262911;
ALTER TABLE t0 MODIFY COLUMN c2 FLOAT NOT NULL;
ALTER TABLE t0 MODIFY COLUMN c5 DECIMAL NULL;
ALTER TABLE t0 MODIFY COLUMN c1 BIGINT DEFAULT -56083770 NOT NULL;
INSERT IGNORE INTO t0 (c1, c2, c5, c4) VALUES (-2051270087, 0.44141045099028775, 0.0, 15523);
UPDATE t0 SET c5 = 870337888;
ALTER TABLE t0 MODIFY COLUMN c1 BIGINT NULL;
INSERT INTO t0 (c2, c5, c4) VALUES (0.004406799693866592, 0.8752311290235516, 14652);
ALTER TABLE t0 MODIFY COLUMN c1 BIGINT NOT NULL;

SELECT /*+ read_from_storage(tikv[t0]) */ * FROM t0 order by 1;
SELECT /*+ read_from_storage(tiflash[t0]) */ * FROM t0 order by 1;
```
<!-- a step by step guide for reproducing the bug. -->

### 2. What did you expect to see? (Required)
The same query returns the same results on both TiKV and TiFlash.
### 3. What did you see instead (Required)
```
mysql> SELECT /*+ read_from_storage(tikv[t0]) */ * FROM t0 order by 1;
ERROR 1105 (HY000): [components/tidb_query_executors/src/table_scan_executor.rs:425]: Data is corrupted, missing data for NOT NULL column (offset = 1)
mysql> SELECT /*+ read_from_storage(tiflash[t0]) */ * FROM t0 order by 1;
+------+-------------+--------------+-----------+-------+
| c0   | c1          | c2           | c5        | c4    |
+------+-------------+--------------+-----------+-------+
| NULL | -2051270087 |   0.44141045 | 870337888 | 15523 |
| NULL |           0 | 0.0044067996 |         1 | 14652 |
+------+-------------+--------------+-----------+-------+
2 rows in set (0.02 sec)
```
